dataIdInfo.idPurp: The mobile home park dataset was generated by geocoding a list of mobile home park addresses supplied to ASU (KER and GRS) by the Arizona Association of Mobile Home Owners (AAMHO). The point locations were then verified by comparing them to other available mobile home data, including Maricopa County assessor data, satellite imagery, google maps, and Maricopa Association of Governments. The purpose is to provide the public a comprehensive dataset of Mobile Home parks or communities in Maricopa County, Arizona. The data were collected and verified in December of 2022.
dataIdInfo.idAbs:
Field Descriptions:

  • parkName

    • The name of the mobile home park. Typically from the original dataset AAMHO provided, however KER and GRS entered values for points that AAMHO did not have or points that were added from different sources (e.g. the Maricopa County Assessor).

  • parkAddress

    • The address of the mobile home park. Typically from the original dataset AAMHO provided, however KER and GRS entered values for points that AAMHO did not have or points that were added from different sources (e.g. the Maricopa County Assessor).

  • parkCity

    • The city that the mobile home park is in. Values are from the original AAMHO dataset.

  • parkState

    • The state that the mobile home park is in. Values are from the original AAMHO dataset.

  • parkZipCod

    • The zip code of the mobile home park. Values are from the original AAMHO dataset.

  • Spaces

    • The number of spaces in that mobile home park. Values are from the original AAMHO dataset.

  • Parcels

    • This field was added by GRS. The possible values are One Parcel, Multiple Parcels, or Individual Parcels. These values represent how many parcels a mobile home park or community are occupying.

  • Status

    • This field was added by GRS. The value is either blank or "Inactive". If inactive, this means that there is evidence the mobile home park existed, but it no longer does.

  • Source

    • This field was added by GRS. The source of the data point, or multiple sources if multiple were used (e.g. AAMHO, MAG, Assessor).

  • AssesPName

    • This field was added by GRS. The value is the park name according to the Maricopa County Assessor's data. This field only has a value if it differs from the park name provided by AAMHO.

  • AssesPAdd

    • This field was added by GRS. The value is the park address according to the Maricopa County Assessor's data. This field only has a value if it differs from the park name provided by AAMHO.
